    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sofas that are oval or round in form, with an upholstered pillar-like back located in the center of the seating area. Intended to stand in the center of the room, with seating around all sides of the sofa. The form developed in France.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000044411/Verlet, French Furniture of the 18th Century (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tipo de sofá francés, ovalado o redondo, con un respaldo semejante a un pilar tapizado en el centro del asiento. Destinado a colocarse en el centro de la habitación.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Frans soort ovale of ronde sofa met een beklede, pilaarachtige rugleuning in het middden van de zitting. Ze zijn bedoeld om in het midden van de kamer te staan.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
